TY  - JOUR
T1  - Mixture Choice Data: Revealing Preferences and Cognition
AU  - Dardanoni, Valentino
AU  - Manzini, Paola
AU  - Mariotti, Marco
AU  - Petri, Henrik
AU  - Tyson, Christopher J.
Y1  - 2022/07/15
PY  - 2022
DA  - 2023/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/721734
DO  - 10.1086/721734
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 687
EP  - 715
VL  - 131
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - Mixture choice data consist of the joint distribution of choices of a group of agents from a collection of menus, comprising the implied stochastic choice function plus any cross-menu correlations. When agents are heterogeneous with respect to both preferences and other aspects of cognition, we show that these two determinants of behavior are identified simultaneously by suitable mixture choice data. We also demonstrate how this finding can be extended to allow for specialized assumptions about cognition, focusing on models of random satisficing thresholds and ?quantal Fechnerian? choice.
AB  - Mixture choice data consist of the joint distribution of choices of a group of agents from a collection of menus, comprising the implied stochastic choice function plus any cross-menu correlations. When agents are heterogeneous with respect to both preferences and other aspects of cognition, we show that these two determinants of behavior are identified simultaneously by suitable mixture choice data. We also demonstrate how this finding can be extended to allow for specialized assumptions about cognition, focusing on models of random satisficing thresholds and ?quantal Fechnerian? choice.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/721734
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/721734
Y2  - 2024/03/20
