N1  - doi: 10.1086/721732
DO  - 10.1086/721732
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 716
EP  - 750
VL  - 131
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - We introduce a flexible framework to study probabilistic choice that accommodates heterogeneous types and bounded rationality. We provide a novel progressive structure for the heterogeneous types to capture heterogeneity due to varying levels of a behavioral trait. Given an order of alternatives, our progressive structure sorts the types by the extent to which they align with this order. Unlike the random-utility model, our model uniquely identifies the heterogeneity, allowing policy makers to perform an improved welfare analysis. As a showcase, we provide characterization of a well-studied type of bounded rationality: ?less-is-more.? In addition, we provide conditions for unique identification of the underlying order for the less-is-more structure.
AB  - We introduce a flexible framework to study probabilistic choice that accommodates heterogeneous types and bounded rationality. We provide a novel progressive structure for the heterogeneous types to capture heterogeneity due to varying levels of a behavioral trait. Given an order of alternatives, our progressive structure sorts the types by the extent to which they align with this order. Unlike the random-utility model, our model uniquely identifies the heterogeneity, allowing policy makers to perform an improved welfare analysis. As a showcase, we provide characterization of a well-studied type of bounded rationality: ?less-is-more.? In addition, we provide conditions for unique identification of the underlying order for the less-is-more structure.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/721732
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/721732
Y2  - 2024/03/20
